    • Method Detail

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        The method to use to compile a Bramspr program. Provide a filename as argument. The filename should refer to a Bramspr file. This method then lexes, parses, context-checks and finally compiles the program to a Java Bytecode .class-file. During this process, the program will be checked for syntactic or contextual errors, and will report those when encountered.
        Parameters:
        args - The filename of the Bramspr-file that is to be compiled.
